{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/blog/dockerize-react/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 740px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7af22b2567ea4d84bf8a43aa328a71dd/83e77/react-docker.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.21621621621622%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"react docker\"\n        title=\"react docker\"\n        src=\"/static/7af22b2567ea4d84bf8a43aa328a71dd/50383/react-docker.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7af22b2567ea4d84bf8a43aa328a71dd/1d79a/react-docker.png 185w,\n/static/7af22b2567ea4d84bf8a43aa328a71dd/1efb2/react-docker.png 370w,\n/static/7af22b2567ea4d84bf8a43aa328a71dd/50383/react-docker.png 740w,\n/static/7af22b2567ea4d84bf8a43aa328a71dd/83e77/react-docker.png 889w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>A quick web-search in your favorite engine will show that Docker is a technology that has increased in popularity and adoption between tech companies. This is due to the flexibility and ease of use making it a must have in every developer tool-belt.</p>\n<p>In this article, I’ll show a simple way to start a React Application and dockerize it - utilizing docker and docker-compose. To complete the steps provided in this tutorial, you’ll need the following tools installed in your computer:</p>\n<h1 id=\"sample-javascr